18/01/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The president of the Council of Europe's (CoE) Congress of Local and Regional Authorities, Giovanni Di Stassi, called on Albanian authorities to fully comply with European standards for local self-government, as he wrapped up a two-day visit to Tirana on Tuesday (17 January).
Di Stassi was trying to resolve a stalemate between the central government and local authorities in Tirana over a road construction project in the capital.
Also Tuesday, police announced the launch of a large-scale operation against drug trafficking in Tirana, Durres and some other towns.
Three people were detained and some 340,000 euros were confiscated.
(Albanian News - 18/01/06;
CoE Web site - 17/01/06)
